1
00:00:36,260 --> 00:00:38,720
This is a simple story...

2
00:00:38,860 --> 00:00:41,370
but not an easy one, to tell.

3
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,370
Like a fable, there is sorrow...

4
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:47,120
and, like a fable, it is full
of wonder and happiness.

5
00:00:50,980 --> 00:00:53,930
I sing what I see. Nothing gets by me.

6
00:00:54,060 --> 00:00:55,690
"Here I am", said I to chaos.

7
00:00:55,820 --> 00:00:58,250
"I am your slave!"
And he: "Good."

8
00:00:58,380 --> 00:01:00,410
"For what?" - said I.

9
00:01:00,580 --> 00:01:04,690
Free in the end, I am!
What good is a caress when bliss...

10
00:01:04,820 --> 00:01:06,450
this man came to possess?

11
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:08,370
Here I am, ready.

12
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:11,170
The trains are gone,
the brakes are gone.

13
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:14,610
And I can resist no more.
Go, sweet Bacchus, take me.

14
00:01:14,740 --> 00:01:17,650
The brakes are gone!
The brakes are gone!

15
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:19,000
I heard you.

16
00:01:19,140 --> 00:01:21,210
- No, they're really gone!
- Hit the brakes!

17
00:01:21,340 --> 00:01:23,170
Weren't you reciting a poem?

18
00:01:24,980 --> 00:01:27,210
It doesn't work!

19
00:01:31,340 --> 00:01:32,930
Brake!

20
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:36,250
We're going to die! The woods!

21
00:01:41,460 --> 00:01:43,410
Brake!

22
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:49,650
The king is coming!

23
00:01:49,780 --> 00:01:52,050
There he is!

24
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:55,730
It's full of people
down there. Straight.

25
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:57,370
We have no brakes!

26
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:00,060
We have no brakes! Move!

27
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:29,650
Go for a walk.

28
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:31,900
Otherwise, we'll get there tomorrow.

29
00:02:32,030 --> 00:02:33,980
I found the screw.

30
00:02:35,070 --> 00:02:36,700
Now what do you need?

31
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:39,660
Nothing. I need ten minutes alone.

32
00:02:39,790 --> 00:02:42,420
All right, I'll leave you alone.

33
00:02:42,550 --> 00:02:44,700
Do you want the screw from before?

34
00:02:44,830 --> 00:02:46,940
No, I want to be alone.

35
00:02:58,070 --> 00:02:59,900
Do I toss out the screw, if I find it?

36
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:02,900
I need ten minutes alone.

37
00:03:03,030 --> 00:03:06,180
I'm washing my hands.

38
00:03:13,510 --> 00:03:16,660
Pretty girl! How's it going?

39
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:18,340
What are you doing?

40
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:20,850
Did your mom put this stuff here?

41
00:03:20,990 --> 00:03:22,700
No, the landlady did.

42
00:03:22,830 --> 00:03:25,460
Is it a market? It's beautiful.

43
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,580
How much is it? How old are you?

44
00:03:28,870 --> 00:03:31,020
- What's your name?
- Eleonora.

45
00:03:31,150 --> 00:03:33,260
Nice to meet you. I'm Prince Guido.

46
00:03:33,390 --> 00:03:37,220
- Prince?
- I'm a prince, I am.

47
00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:39,140
All this is mine.

48
00:03:39,270 --> 00:03:41,420
Here starts the prince's principate.

49
00:03:41,550 --> 00:03:43,780
I'll call this place Addis Ababa.

50
00:03:43,910 --> 00:03:48,380
I'll change it all. Out go
the cows, in come the camels.

51
00:03:48,510 --> 00:03:50,540
Camels?

52
00:03:50,670 --> 00:03:52,780
Even a few hippopotamus.

53
00:03:52,910 --> 00:03:54,940
I must go. I'm meeting
with the princess.

54
00:03:55,070 --> 00:03:57,530
- When?
- Now!

55
00:04:02,070 --> 00:04:04,060
Good morning, Princess!

56
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:07,470
How frightening. I almost
killed myself. Did I hurt you?

57
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,150
I've never been better.

58
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,830
Do you always leave the house like this?

59
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,670
I wanted to burn that
wasps nest, but I got stung.

60
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:16,100
A wasp stung you? There? Allow me.

61
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,510
Hold still, Princess.

62
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:20,990
A wasp's poison is very dangerous.

63
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:22,710
You have to get it out.

64
00:04:22,840 --> 00:04:26,070
- Lie down. It'll take a while.
- No, thank you.

65
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:31,230
- Did you get stung anywhere else?
- No, thank you.

66
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:33,790
What a place here! It's beautiful!

67
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:36,750
Pigeons fly, women fall from
the sky. I'm moving here!

68
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:40,630
It's all his! He wants to fill it,
with camels! He's a prince!

69
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:42,550
Exactly.

70
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:45,710
Prince Guido at your service, Princess.

71
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:47,550
I'm coming!

72
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,630
Goodbye, then.

73
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:53,070
- How can I thank you?
- There's no need.

74
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:55,190
If you really want to thank me...

75
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:58,550
I'll take some eggs, to make
a nice omelet, for my squire.

76
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,670
Take whatever you want. It's all yours.

77
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,990
Thank you!

78
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:05,990
I'll take two... six.
All right? I'll make a nice omelet.

79
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:09,110
Goodbye, Eleonora! My regards, Princess.

80
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,070
Farewell.

81
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:17,150
Here I am, Nuvolari!
Tonight's special: Omelet!

82
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,190
All camels here!

83
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:31,260
- Where is this house?
- Turn left. We're almost there.

84
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,350
Is your uncle sleeping with us?

85
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,430
He's lived in the hotel for 30 years.

86
00:05:35,470 --> 00:05:36,550
He's the head maitre.

87
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:39,550
He's lending us the house.
He uses it for storage.

88
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,870
There. We're here.

89
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:44,150
That's Robin Hood, my uncle's horse.

90
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:46,270
Here's my uncle's buggy
and my uncle's house.

91
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,230
And inside is my uncle.

92
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:51,920
Hello, dear uncle!
Here we are! Hurry, it's late.

93
00:05:52,050 --> 00:05:53,840
Here we are. The car broke down!

94
00:05:59,370 --> 00:06:01,320
Uncle!

95
00:06:06,330 --> 00:06:08,360
- Barbarians.
- Who were they?

96
00:06:08,490 --> 00:06:10,640
- Barbarians.
- Why didn't you cry for help?

97
00:06:10,770 --> 00:06:13,330
Silence is the most powerful cry.

98
00:06:13,450 --> 00:06:15,240
Is he your poet friend?

99
00:06:15,370 --> 00:06:17,640
My name is Ferruccio.
I'm also an upholsterer.

100
00:06:19,090 --> 00:06:22,360
Here you are. It's an old
storehouse, full of odds and ends.

101
00:06:22,490 --> 00:06:25,840
An old passion...
an odd and end in itself!

102
00:06:25,970 --> 00:06:28,200
What's all this stuff for?

103
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:32,400
You can stay as long as you want.
It's not easy to be a waiter.

104
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:35,600
That's the bed. Legend has it,
Garibaldi slept there.

105
00:06:35,730 --> 00:06:37,640
Nothing is more necessary,
than the unnecessary.

106
00:06:37,770 --> 00:06:39,040
Barbarians.

107
00:06:39,170 --> 00:06:42,640
The town hall is on Via Sestani,
to the right after the colonnade.

108
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:46,200
The bathroom, equipped with
the invention, of Mr. Bidet.

109
00:06:46,330 --> 00:06:50,030
There are a few books here,
among which, The Life of Petrarch.

110
00:06:50,170 --> 00:06:54,960
The kitchen is in there. This is a
velocipede, commonly called a bike.

111
00:06:55,090 --> 00:06:59,120
I have to get back to the hotel.
There's only one key. Don't lose it.

112
00:06:59,930 --> 00:07:04,000
It's so good to see you.
I'm coming, Robin Hood!

113
00:07:07,410 --> 00:07:08,880
What an uncle!

114
00:07:10,570 --> 00:07:12,480
Look at this!

115
00:07:14,050 --> 00:07:17,880
Didn't I tell you? We're in a city.
You can do whatever you want.

116
00:07:18,010 --> 00:07:20,680
If you want to do something, you do it.

117
00:07:20,810 --> 00:07:23,190
You want to let yourself go?
You want to yell? Yell!

118
00:07:25,850 --> 00:07:27,640
Stop it! What are you, crazy?

119
00:07:27,770 --> 00:07:30,600
You can not act,
like you do in the country.

120
00:07:30,630 --> 00:07:32,450
You've been yelling like a madman.

121
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,160
You can't yell!

122
00:07:34,290 --> 00:07:36,000
Mary! The key!

123
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:41,800
See? You can't yell.

124
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:45,530
Understand? If you stopped
thinking, so much about poetry...

125
00:07:45,660 --> 00:07:49,360
you'd make your father happier
and you'd make more money than him.

126
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,490
That's right, Oreste.
That's what I tell him too.

127
00:07:51,620 --> 00:07:53,730
You have to settle down!

128
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:56,450
What a nice hat. How does it look?

129
00:07:56,580 --> 00:07:59,090
- Nice. How does it look?
- Nice, but it's mine.

130
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:01,210
When do I start working?

131
00:08:01,340 --> 00:08:03,530
You're already late. Right away!

132
00:08:03,660 --> 00:08:06,220
Get that armchair and
take it to the workshop.

133
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:10,370
- That one?
- That one. And be careful!

134
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:13,250
Good. I'm going to
the town hall. Goodbye.

135
00:08:13,380 --> 00:08:16,090
Goodbye, and behave yourselves...

136
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:18,600
because these are hard times.

137
00:08:18,740 --> 00:08:20,330
Hard, hard times!

138
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:22,290
They're hard times?

139
00:08:22,420 --> 00:08:25,330
Why, what are your political views?

140
00:08:25,460 --> 00:08:28,530
Benito! Adolph! Be good!

141
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:30,450
What did you say?

142
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:34,650
I said, how are things going?

143
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:36,650
Goodbye, then.

144
00:08:36,780 --> 00:08:38,330
Careful! You'll break the legs!

145
00:08:39,980 --> 00:08:41,090
Goodbye!

146
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:51,170
He pulled it off. He took my hat.
I'll find him though.

147
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:53,490
Benito, you're going to get a slap!

148
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:59,210
I need to do the whole bureaucratic
procedure, to open a bookstore.

149
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:01,610
- Does it take a long time?
- Years.

150
00:09:01,740 --> 00:09:03,530
Then we'd better open a file now.

151
00:09:03,660 --> 00:09:07,090
First you apply, and the
department head has to sign it.

152
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:13,450
I almost scrambled my eggs.
I've had them since yesterday.

153
00:09:13,580 --> 00:09:16,490
I forgot about them. Thank God,
they didn't break. Take note.

154
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:18,330
I, the undersigned, Guido Orefice...

155
00:09:18,460 --> 00:09:21,170
- am applying to open...
- He can't sign it now!

156
00:09:22,380 --> 00:09:24,330
What's going on?

157
00:09:24,460 --> 00:09:26,840
I need your signature
to open a bookstore.

158
00:09:26,980 --> 00:09:29,900
- Miss, what's going on?
- Mr. Rodolfo, I told him.

159
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:32,380
- Just one signature.
- No, I can't.

160
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:34,890
My substitute will be
here, in an hour. Ask him.

161
00:09:35,030 --> 00:09:38,540
- All I need is a signature.
- We close at one here!

162
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:40,620
It's ten to one.

163
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:42,100
File a complaint.

164
00:09:43,430 --> 00:09:46,220
Boy, is he nasty.

165
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:49,780
To sign a paper, open a file,
all he had to do was...

166
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:52,860
Now I have to wait one
hour, for his substitute.

167
00:09:52,990 --> 00:09:55,340
I'm filing a complaint.
Write, "I, the undersigned..."

168
00:09:58,670 --> 00:10:00,460
What a wallop!

169
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:06,340
Are you hurt? I'll help you.

170
00:10:06,470 --> 00:10:08,060
Come here. I didn't do it on purpose.

171
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:09,700
Don't touch me!

172
00:10:10,990 --> 00:10:13,860
You can forget about your bookshop!

173
00:10:14,910 --> 00:10:16,050
No, the eggs!

174
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:21,100
You scoundrel! I'll kill you!

175
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:31,580
Out of the way!

176
00:10:38,230 --> 00:10:40,580
Good morning, Princess.

177
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:44,740
I wonder, if we'll ever bump
into each other, standing up.

178
00:10:44,870 --> 00:10:47,460
Excuse me, but I've got to run.

179
00:10:47,590 --> 00:10:50,050
Farewell, Princess!

180
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:05,410
- Chicken.
- That's easy.

181
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:08,220
It's served whole,
bottom down on the plate.

182
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:10,100
"Will you cut it for me?"
"Naturally."

183
00:11:10,230 --> 00:11:13,670
I stick the blade under the wing,
then I rip off the drumstick.

184
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:16,430
I cut the meat along the
bottom of the breastbone.

185
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:19,120
- Off go the wings, breast and skin.
- Lobster.

186
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:21,540
Piece of cake, Uncle.

187
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:24,590
I stick the wing under the leg.

188
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:27,070
Off goes the leg. I rip off
the lobster, stick the...

189
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,270
Lobster is a crustacean.

190
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:34,590
Off goes the crust... of the crustacean.

191
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:39,660
Off go the crust and antennae.
Who eats the antennae?

192
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,510
Off go the antennae,
off goes the lobster.

193
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:44,070
There's nothing left.

194
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,910
We're out of lobster,
but the chicken is delicious.

195
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:52,270
- I don't remember how to do lobster.
- You serve it as is.

196
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,350
There's no need to touch it!

197
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:56,670
That's too easy.
That's why I didn't remember.

198
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:58,470
- Continue.
- Behavior!

199
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:00,590
Stand by. Still, like this.

200
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,430
"Waiter?" - "Yes?"

201
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:04,990
In position. Stand by behavior. Waiter!

202
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:15,420
Why only me? There must be,
other waiters, right?

203
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:19,590
Bowing! Piece of cake.

204
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:24,350
You bow down, further.

205
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:28,260
Like this, at a 45 degree angle,
just like a champagne bottle.

206
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,270
45 degrees, even 50 or 55.

207
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:34,190
90 degrees. A right angle. 180.

208
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,550
How far do I bow down?
180 degrees? Like this?

209
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:40,510
Think of a sunflower.
They bow to the sun.

210
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:43,070
But if you see some,
that are too bowed down...

211
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,710
it means they're dead!

212
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:47,110
You're serving. You're not a servant.

213
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:49,310
Serving is a supreme art.

214
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,790
God is the first servant.

215
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:54,950
God serves men, but he's
not a servant, to men.

216
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:58,990
- There was no button here.
- It doesn't go there, silly.

217
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:02,270
I have to take the car back to Pop.
He's counting on it.

218
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:04,270
You'll take it back in a month or so.

219
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:07,160
No, I've got to get it
back soon. You know why?

220
00:13:08,410 --> 00:13:09,880
Why?

221
00:13:16,330 --> 00:13:19,520
- What? What time is it?
- Were you sleeping?

222
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:21,880
Of course I was.

223
00:13:22,010 --> 00:13:24,720
You fell asleep while talking to me!

224
00:13:24,850 --> 00:13:27,080
- How did you do that?
- Schopenhauer.

225
00:13:27,210 --> 00:13:28,880
Who?

226
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:32,440
Schopenhauer says that with willpower,
you can do anything.

227
00:13:32,570 --> 00:13:34,360
"I am what I want to be."

228
00:13:34,490 --> 00:13:37,480
Right now I want to sleep,
so I was saying to myself...

229
00:13:37,610 --> 00:13:39,760
"I'm sleeping, sleeping",
and I fell asleep.

230
00:13:41,210 --> 00:13:43,000
Amazing. And it's simple too.

231
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:46,200
I want to try too.
I'm sleeping, sleeping, sleeping...

232
00:13:48,690 --> 00:13:51,200
Don't move your hands.
You're not a juggler.

233
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:54,560
It's a matter of thought.
It's serious, and it takes time.

234
00:13:54,690 --> 00:13:56,520
We'll talk about it tomorrow.

235
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,320
Amazing, though.

236
00:14:00,970 --> 00:14:02,640
Wake up.

237
00:14:02,770 --> 00:14:05,230
Wake up.

238
00:14:07,290 --> 00:14:09,080
What is it now? What are you doing?

239
00:14:09,210 --> 00:14:11,320
- It totally works!
- What works?

240
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:15,280
Schopenhauer. You know
what I just said? "Wake up".

241
00:14:15,410 --> 00:14:18,560
Bam, you woke up.
This theory is incredible.

242
00:14:18,690 --> 00:14:21,040
- How does it work?
- You were yelling in my ear!

243
00:14:21,170 --> 00:14:23,840
That's why I woke up.

244
00:14:23,970 --> 00:14:27,160
- So I should say it quieter.
- Don't say it at all!

245
00:14:30,730 --> 00:14:32,720
It's deep. You have to think it.

246
00:14:37,130 --> 00:14:39,000
Why are you running? Slow down!

247
00:14:39,090 --> 00:14:40,480
Hurry up. It's late!

248
00:14:40,610 --> 00:14:42,520
Mary, the key!

249
00:14:44,810 --> 00:14:46,520
Every morning, she throws the key.

250
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:47,920
Look!

251
00:14:48,050 --> 00:14:50,730
There's that teacher.
Boy, is she pretty.

252
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:54,010
I even dreamt about her.
Come with me. I'll introduce you.

253
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:57,050
- Holy smokes! Stay still!
- What is it?

254
00:14:57,180 --> 00:14:58,450
Don't move!

255
00:14:58,580 --> 00:15:02,530
The one in the car.
He's that jerk the eggs fell on.

256
00:15:02,660 --> 00:15:04,810
He'll kill me if he sees me. Be good.

257
00:15:04,940 --> 00:15:07,010
- What's he doing?
- He's talking.

258
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:09,090
- What's he saying?
- How do I know?

259
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:12,570
- What's he doing?
- He's saying goodbye.

260
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:16,010
He's got a car just
like mine! There he is!

261
00:15:16,140 --> 00:15:18,850
Don't move. He'll kill me if he sees me!

262
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:20,330
Stay still, Ferruccio.

263
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:26,280
Good morning, Princess!

264
00:15:27,980 --> 00:15:31,010
It's you again. How do you do this?

265
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:34,570
This is the princess, who fell
from the sky into my arms.

266
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:37,810
Is he the one, who sucked the
stinger out of your thigh?

267
00:15:37,940 --> 00:15:40,890
Yes. We keep meeting like this.
You just suddenly show up.

268
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:44,170
We could make plans to meet.

269
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:46,680
- Tonight at 8:00?
- No, it's nicer this way.

270
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,330
Let's go, Dora. You'll be late.

271
00:15:50,660 --> 00:15:53,040
I hope we meet again suddenly.

272
00:15:53,180 --> 00:15:56,210
Farewell, Princess!

273
00:15:56,340 --> 00:15:58,370
Did you see her? She's pretty, huh?

274
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,690
She likes it when I suddenly appear.

275
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:10,840
I don't believe it.

276
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:13,250
"Obscurity."

277
00:16:13,380 --> 00:16:14,930
You're a genius!

278
00:16:15,060 --> 00:16:17,890
"The bigger it is, the less you see it."

279
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:19,610
Solution: Obscurity.

280
00:16:19,740 --> 00:16:22,300
Marvelous. Did you make that riddle up?

281
00:16:22,420 --> 00:16:26,850
No, but you solved it in five minutes.
It took me eight days.

282
00:16:26,980 --> 00:16:28,530
Obscurity!

283
00:16:28,660 --> 00:16:31,290
Salmon, salad and a glass of white wine.

284
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:33,490
Listen to this one, Guido.

285
00:16:34,550 --> 00:16:37,460
If I may, it's my turn.

286
00:16:37,590 --> 00:16:39,540
My pop told me this,
when I was a wee boy.

287
00:16:39,670 --> 00:16:42,130
"The dwarves and Snow White,
sit down for a bite.

288
00:16:42,270 --> 00:16:46,540
How fast can you guess,
what she serves her guests next?"

289
00:16:49,830 --> 00:16:51,980
It sounds refined.

290
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:54,100
I want to solve it, right now.

291
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:57,420
- Eat first or it'll get cold.
- I don't want to. It's too late.

292
00:16:57,550 --> 00:16:59,580
Salad, salmon, white wine. It's light.

293
00:16:59,710 --> 00:17:01,500
The dwarves...

294
00:17:02,830 --> 00:17:04,460
and Snow White.

295
00:17:07,870 --> 00:17:10,700
- Is the kitchen closed?
- Everybody's gone. Why?

296
00:17:10,830 --> 00:17:13,780
A gentleman from Rome is here,
from the Ministry. He wants to eat.

297
00:17:13,910 --> 00:17:15,420
The kitchen is closed.

298
00:17:15,550 --> 00:17:17,900
Oh, well, he would have
given you a good tip.

299
00:17:18,030 --> 00:17:19,820
The kitchen is open.

300
00:17:20,590 --> 00:17:22,060
Come right in.

301
00:17:30,830 --> 00:17:33,020
Doctor, you're not eating anything?

302
00:17:35,630 --> 00:17:37,180
"The dwarves and Snow White..."

303
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:42,580
I know the kitchen is closed.
Maybe a cold dish.

304
00:17:42,710 --> 00:17:47,180
- It's all delicious. Take your pick.
- Something light.

305
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:50,060
Well, we've got meat,
a nice heavy steak...

306
00:17:50,190 --> 00:17:53,380
lamb, kidneys, some
greasy breaded liver.

307
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:55,810
- Otherwise, there's fish.
- Fish.

308
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:59,140
We have... a nice fatty turbot...

309
00:17:59,270 --> 00:18:02,340
eel, stuffed with fatty sausage,
and greased with Grand Marnier...

310
00:18:02,470 --> 00:18:04,100
or some lean salmon...

311
00:18:04,230 --> 00:18:06,460
The salmon, thank you.

312
00:18:06,590 --> 00:18:09,020
- Side dish?
- There's a side dish too?

313
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:13,020
Of course. We have very,
very fried mushrooms...

314
00:18:13,150 --> 00:18:16,620
buttered potatoes in Nancy butter,
with a flaky sauce...

315
00:18:16,750 --> 00:18:21,340
Is there a small, light salad?
If not, nothing.

316
00:18:21,470 --> 00:18:26,060
A light salad? What a pity.
The very, very fried mushrooms...

317
00:18:26,190 --> 00:18:28,660
were out of this world.
So, a light salad...

318
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:31,150
a lean salmon and a glass of white wine.

319
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:33,430
Perfect. As soon as possible.

320
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:35,350
I'll do my best.

321
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:53,510
"How fast can you guess,
what she serves her guests next?"

322
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:54,830
Right.

323
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:58,790
- "The dwarves and Snow White."
- Good night, Doctor.

324
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,950
Good night, genius.

325
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,120
What did he say?

326
00:19:04,130 --> 00:19:06,550
The dwarves? What is he, drunk?

327
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,310
It's a riddle. "Seven seconds".

328
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:13,910
"Seven seconds" is the solution.
"The dwarves and Snow White."

329
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:16,150
If there are seven dwarves dining...

330
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,510
and she serves seconds,
that means "seven seconds".

331
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:23,190
Doctor Lessing is a physician,
a very serious person.

332
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:26,390
But he's obsessed with riddles.
He loses sleep over them.

333
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:31,750
Excuse me, the "Francesco
Petrarca" school.

334
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:34,340
The elementary school?

335
00:19:34,370 --> 00:19:36,550
A friend of mine teaches there.
It's beautiful.

336
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,870
It's not far from here. Why?

337
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,300
Good. I can sleep an extra half hour.

338
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:44,710
Do you have to go, to that
school, tomorrow morning?

339
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:46,470
They're expecting me at 8:30.

340
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:55,830
Please, children, silence!
A moment of attention.

341
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:58,870
The inspector from Rome,
will be here shortly.

342
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,990
I want to make a good impression on him.

343
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:04,590
Listen very quietly and
carefully to what he says.

344
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:07,790
He'll tell us some very important
things about our beautiful country.

345
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:11,440
The inspector is here, ma'am.

346
00:20:11,570 --> 00:20:14,080
He's already here? He's early!

347
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:15,720
Sit down, Roberto!

348
00:20:20,090 --> 00:20:22,470
All rise!

349
00:20:26,530 --> 00:20:28,360
Good morning, Princess.

350
00:20:31,290 --> 00:20:34,720
Good morning, Mr. Inspector.
I'm the principal.

351
00:20:34,850 --> 00:20:36,960
These are some of our teachers.

352
00:20:39,490 --> 00:20:40,800
Good.

353
00:20:43,010 --> 00:20:44,320
Therefore...

354
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:49,640
How many years have you
taught, in this school district?

355
00:20:49,770 --> 00:20:51,080
Sixteen.

356
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:56,000
Are you up to date, with the ongoing...

357
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:58,160
school program, approved
by the Ministry this year?

358
00:20:58,290 --> 00:20:59,600
Yes.

359
00:21:01,450 --> 00:21:05,480
Did you read the bulletin,
regarding childhood hygiene?

360
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:07,400
Of course.

361
00:21:09,570 --> 00:21:11,800
What are you doing on Sunday?

362
00:21:11,930 --> 00:21:16,480
No, I mean, Sunday is St. Mary's Day.
What are you doing?

363
00:21:16,610 --> 00:21:18,840
I'm going to the theater.

364
00:21:20,810 --> 00:21:23,040
- To see what?
- Offenbach.

365
00:21:23,170 --> 00:21:25,120
Right, they're playing Offenbach.

366
00:21:28,570 --> 00:21:30,360
Fine. Well...

367
00:21:31,370 --> 00:21:34,120
Thank you very much, and
goodbye. I just came to...

368
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:35,640
We know.

369
00:21:35,770 --> 00:21:37,920
As you know, the inspector...

370
00:21:38,050 --> 00:21:40,680
came from Rome to talk to us
about the race manifesto...

371
00:21:40,810 --> 00:21:44,040
signed by the most well
versed Italian scientists.

372
00:21:44,170 --> 00:21:47,200
He will, and we're very honored...

373
00:21:47,330 --> 00:21:49,630
demonstrate to us that our race...

374
00:21:49,770 --> 00:21:51,560
is a superior race...

375
00:21:51,690 --> 00:21:53,760
the best of all.

376
00:21:53,890 --> 00:21:55,610
Take your seats.

377
00:21:57,420 --> 00:21:59,880
Go ahead, Inspector.

378
00:22:00,020 --> 00:22:02,580
- Our race...
- Is superior.

379
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:04,010
Naturally!

380
00:22:05,260 --> 00:22:07,210
Our race is superior.

381
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:10,730
I've just come from Rome,
right this minute...

382
00:22:10,860 --> 00:22:14,010
to come and tell you in order
that, you'll know, children...

383
00:22:14,140 --> 00:22:15,930
that our race is a superior one.

384
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:17,810
I was...

385
00:22:17,940 --> 00:22:21,930
chosen, I was, by racist
Italian scientists...

386
00:22:22,060 --> 00:22:23,850
in order to demonstrate...

387
00:22:23,980 --> 00:22:26,490
how superior our race is.

388
00:22:26,620 --> 00:22:30,160
Why did they pick me, children?

389
00:22:31,980 --> 00:22:34,170
Must I tell you?

390
00:22:36,820 --> 00:22:38,610
Where can you find...

391
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:41,730
someone more handsome than me?

392
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:45,560
Justly so, there is silence.
I'm an original "superior race"...

393
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:47,010
pure Aryan.

394
00:22:47,140 --> 00:22:48,810
Children.

395
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:51,770
Let's start with something that one says:
"What's so big about that?"

396
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:56,170
The ear. Look at the
perfection of this ear.

397
00:22:56,300 --> 00:22:58,680
Left auricle...

398
00:22:58,820 --> 00:23:01,250
with a pendant little bell at the end.

399
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:04,130
Check it out. Movable cartilage.

400
00:23:04,260 --> 00:23:05,770
Bendable.

401
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:08,610
Find two ears more beautiful
than these and I'll leave!

402
00:23:08,740 --> 00:23:12,410
But you have to show me them.
They dream about these in France!

403
00:23:12,540 --> 00:23:15,370
Races exists, children. You bet they do!

404
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,540
But let's continue.

405
00:23:16,570 --> 00:23:18,490
I want to show you something else.

406
00:23:18,620 --> 00:23:20,210
Pay attention.

407
00:23:21,460 --> 00:23:23,450
He said Inspector?

408
00:23:23,580 --> 00:23:25,410
From Rome?

409
00:23:26,820 --> 00:23:28,610
The belly button!

410
00:23:30,860 --> 00:23:33,890
Take a look at this
belly button! What a knot!

411
00:23:34,020 --> 00:23:36,170
But you can't untie it,
not even with your teeth!

412
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:39,050
Those racist scientists tried it.
Not a chance!

413
00:23:39,180 --> 00:23:42,010
This is an Italian belly button.
It's part of our race!

414
00:23:42,140 --> 00:23:44,050
Check out this style!

415
00:23:44,180 --> 00:23:48,780
Look at these muscles:
Caps, biceps, triceps!

416
00:23:48,910 --> 00:23:51,700
Look at this beauty! Admire this hip!

417
00:23:56,070 --> 00:23:58,740
Just look at the movement!

418
00:23:58,870 --> 00:23:59,980
Gentlemen!

419
00:24:02,350 --> 00:24:04,220
I must say goodbye now.

420
00:24:04,350 --> 00:24:07,220
I have to go. I have an appointment.

421
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:09,910
I'll make my Aryan exit
and bid you farewell.

422
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:11,740
Farewell! The belly button!

423
00:24:14,230 --> 00:24:16,900
I'll see you in Venice, Princess.

424
00:25:17,430 --> 00:25:19,260
I can only hear out of this ear.

425
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:40,150
Look at me, Princess.

426
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:42,070
Go on, I'm down here.

427
00:25:43,960 --> 00:25:46,550
Look at me, Princess.

428
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:04,480
Turn around, Princess.

429
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:08,110
Turn around, around...

430
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:47,030
- Can we get a chocolate ice cream?
- Yes, but we'll have to be quick.

431
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,270
Why?

432
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,810
We have to be at the Prefect's at eight.

433
00:26:50,850 --> 00:26:52,390
We were invited to dinner.

434
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,190
- Where?
- At the Prefect's.

435
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:57,990
Have pity on me, Lord.
Let it not be true.

436
00:26:58,120 --> 00:27:01,070
- Another dinner at the Prefect's?
- Your mother is coming too.

437
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:02,510
Bingo!

438
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:04,420
Let's us just go to dinner.

439
00:27:04,450 --> 00:27:07,070
We'll stop by the Prefect's for coffee.

440
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,150
I'm not coming!

441
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:11,710
All right, I heard you!
I'll tell him we're not going.

442
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:13,950
It'll just be me and you.

443
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:18,240
- Good evening, Rodolfo!
- Good evening, Mr. Prefect.

444
00:27:19,450 --> 00:27:21,910
I'll see you later at my house.
I'll expect you at 8:00.

445
00:27:22,050 --> 00:27:23,840
We'll be there at 8:00 sharp.

446
00:27:28,090 --> 00:27:30,280
Where is she? Did you see her?

447
00:27:30,410 --> 00:27:32,640
- She has to be here.
- You're here?

448
00:27:34,250 --> 00:27:36,680
On time tomorrow, got it?

449
00:27:36,810 --> 00:27:39,080
Did you take that stuff out of the car?

450
00:27:39,210 --> 00:27:41,670
It's silk. Don't ruin it.
Be very careful.

451
00:27:43,450 --> 00:27:45,800
- What an opera.
- Beautiful!

452
00:27:48,250 --> 00:27:50,920
Is that one of your curtains?

453
00:27:51,050 --> 00:27:53,960
No, it must be one of my colleague's.

454
00:27:56,450 --> 00:27:58,360
He took my hat again!

455
00:27:59,370 --> 00:28:01,520
- Let's go.
- Don't you see how it's raining?

456
00:28:01,650 --> 00:28:04,210
- You go get the car.
- It's right around the corner.

457
00:28:04,330 --> 00:28:06,560
All right, you wait here.

458
00:28:06,690 --> 00:28:09,880
I'll pull up right here and toot.

459
00:28:10,970 --> 00:28:13,080
Give me the key!

460
00:28:13,210 --> 00:28:15,240
Not the house key! The car key!

461
00:28:16,810 --> 00:28:18,840
The car key? Are you crazy?

462
00:28:18,970 --> 00:28:21,480
Keep him busy, you know,
the jerk, the eggs fell on.

463
00:28:21,610 --> 00:28:23,960
Keep him busy as long as you can.
I'll see you tonight.

464
00:28:24,090 --> 00:28:26,160
Inside the car there's... Go slow!

465
00:28:42,690 --> 00:28:44,960
The least you could have done,
is come get me with the umbrella.

466
00:28:45,090 --> 00:28:47,840
You're just plain rude.
Look what a mess I am.

467
00:28:47,970 --> 00:28:51,800
Plus, dinner at the Prefect's,
gets me so nervous!

468
00:28:53,290 --> 00:28:55,560
I knew it. I've got the hiccups.

469
00:28:55,690 --> 00:28:59,640
I always get them, when I'm made
to do something, I don't want to.

470
00:28:59,770 --> 00:29:02,680
Don't you know, that it takes
so little, to make me happy?

471
00:29:02,810 --> 00:29:05,400
A chocolate ice cream,
is enough! Even two!

472
00:29:05,530 --> 00:29:08,840
A nice walk together and
then whatever happens, happens.

473
00:29:08,970 --> 00:29:11,090
Instead you...

474
00:29:12,180 --> 00:29:13,970
Good morning, Princess!

475
00:29:15,820 --> 00:29:18,490
This is incredible.
You owe me an explanation.

476
00:29:18,620 --> 00:29:21,330
No, you're the one who
owes me an explanation!

477
00:29:21,460 --> 00:29:24,250
I stop under a roof and you
fall from the sky into my arms.

478
00:29:24,380 --> 00:29:27,130
I fall off my bicycle
and end up in your arms.

479
00:29:27,260 --> 00:29:30,930
I do an inspection at school,
and there you are again!

480
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:33,210
You even turn up in my dreams.

481
00:29:33,340 --> 00:29:37,930
Will you leave me alone?
You've really got a crush on me.

482
00:29:38,060 --> 00:29:39,850
I don't blame you, but...

483
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:43,290
All right. At this point,
I give in. You win.

484
00:29:43,420 --> 00:29:46,370
Where shall we go, Princess?
To the sea! Do you like the sea?

485
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:49,490
Yes, but they're waiting for me,
at the theater. Take me back.

486
00:29:50,620 --> 00:29:51,810
What's happening?

487
00:29:51,940 --> 00:29:55,530
Princess, do you know how to
turn on the windshield wipers?

488
00:29:55,660 --> 00:29:57,490
Step on the brakes!

489
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:01,810
Have no fear! Hang on to me!

490
00:30:01,940 --> 00:30:03,730
It's broken!

491
00:30:03,860 --> 00:30:05,770
When did you learn to drive?

492
00:30:05,900 --> 00:30:08,170
- Ten minutes ago.
- I thought it was less than that.

493
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:11,170
- The top doesn't close.
- The door won't open.

494
00:30:11,300 --> 00:30:13,930
Wait! We're stuck!

495
00:30:14,060 --> 00:30:16,520
We'll get out of here.
I'll take care of it.

496
00:30:16,660 --> 00:30:18,690
The important thing is,
that you don't get wet.

497
00:30:18,820 --> 00:30:20,810
Cover yourself with this.

498
00:30:20,940 --> 00:30:22,890
Take it. We'll get out of here now.

499
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:26,170
I'll take care of everything.

500
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:29,650
Here we go.

501
00:30:30,700 --> 00:30:32,890
Step right out, Princess.

502
00:30:35,780 --> 00:30:37,770
There! Step right out!

