754
00:49:35,490 --> 00:49:37,920
- Is that man with you?
- Yes. Let's go.

755
00:49:38,050 --> 00:49:39,320
All right.

756
00:49:39,450 --> 00:49:41,080
- I'm coming too.
- No.

757
00:49:41,210 --> 00:49:42,360
You stay here. It won't
take long, will it?

758
00:49:42,480 --> 00:49:44,280
Not long at all.

759
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:47,710
Joshua, make sure you
treat the customers good!

760
00:49:47,850 --> 00:49:50,440
I'll be right back.

761
00:50:50,180 --> 00:50:53,220
- I'll take this one.
- It costs five lire.

762
00:50:53,340 --> 00:50:56,810
No, it says ten lire.

763
00:50:56,940 --> 00:50:59,580
Everything's half price.

764
00:51:01,750 --> 00:51:05,860
Give this to your mom and
tell her, it's from Grandma.

765
00:51:05,980 --> 00:51:09,370
I've never seen my grandma before.

766
00:51:09,500 --> 00:51:12,020
- Would you like to meet her?
- Yes.

767
00:51:13,270 --> 00:51:14,940
You'll meet her tomorrow.

768
00:51:15,070 --> 00:51:17,020
- Tomorrow?
- Yes.

769
00:51:17,150 --> 00:51:19,300
Because tomorrow is your birthday...

770
00:51:19,430 --> 00:51:21,550
and your grandma will come.
and bring you a nice present.

771
00:51:21,670 --> 00:51:24,620
A new tank?

772
00:51:25,380 --> 00:51:26,790
No, a surprise.

773
00:51:26,910 --> 00:51:28,700
Give the letter to your mom.

774
00:51:30,190 --> 00:51:31,780
Bye, Joshua.

775
00:51:31,910 --> 00:51:33,580
You forgot your change, Grandma.

776
00:51:40,150 --> 00:51:41,100
Thank you.

777
00:51:42,190 --> 00:51:44,390
- When are you coming?
- In an hour or so.

778
00:51:44,510 --> 00:51:47,150
I'm going to stop by my uncle,
to see if he'll bring some leftovers.

779
00:51:48,470 --> 00:51:51,270
- Then what did Grandma say?
- She's coming tomorrow.

780
00:51:53,790 --> 00:51:55,020
It's about time!

781
00:51:55,150 --> 00:51:56,900
JEWISH STORE

782
00:51:57,110 --> 00:51:59,780
- It's time for your bath now.
- I don't want to take one.

783
00:51:59,910 --> 00:52:02,630
- Go take a bath.
- I took one on Friday.

784
00:52:02,750 --> 00:52:04,270
He's right.

785
00:52:04,390 --> 00:52:06,190
You change your shirt.

786
00:52:06,310 --> 00:52:08,590
- I changed it on Thursday!
- Don't forget the flowers!

787
00:52:08,710 --> 00:52:11,020
They're outside. I already picked them.

788
00:52:11,150 --> 00:52:14,940
- I'll come with you, Pop!
- You have to take a bath, stubborn!

789
00:52:15,070 --> 00:52:17,460
I don't want to take one!

790
00:52:17,590 --> 00:52:19,400
Hurry up. I have to go pick Grandma up.

791
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:29,800
- Where do you want the flowers?
- Set them down. I'll be right there.

792
00:52:39,770 --> 00:52:41,680
I took one on Friday!

793
00:52:46,690 --> 00:52:48,520
Do you know where Joshua is?

794
00:52:48,650 --> 00:52:50,610
He must be in there.

795
00:52:50,730 --> 00:52:52,520
Will you put those things, in order?

796
00:52:52,650 --> 00:52:53,880
Why don't you show me, the flowers?

797
00:52:53,910 --> 00:52:54,720
They look so beautiful.

798
00:52:54,850 --> 00:52:57,410
They are. I'll bring them right over.
You want to see the flowers?

799
00:52:57,530 --> 00:53:00,300
I'll make them, come right over.

800
00:53:00,330 --> 00:53:01,520
Come, flowers!

801
00:53:01,650 --> 00:53:03,240
Come, nightstand!

802
00:53:03,370 --> 00:53:06,170
Schopenhauer, willpower, I want
the nightstand to come here.

803
00:53:06,290 --> 00:53:08,720
Nightstand, come.

804
00:53:10,130 --> 00:53:12,440
Stop, nightstand!

805
00:53:12,570 --> 00:53:15,650
The nightstand seems, very dirty to me.

806
00:53:15,770 --> 00:53:18,840
Good morning, Princess!

807
00:53:23,140 --> 00:53:25,090
He can already read and write?

808
00:53:25,220 --> 00:53:27,680
- For over a year now.
- You did a good job.

809
00:53:27,810 --> 00:53:29,770
We're here.

810
00:53:29,890 --> 00:53:31,800
I'll help you get out.

811
00:53:31,940 --> 00:53:33,730
No, I can do it myself.

812
00:53:50,660 --> 00:53:52,730
Dora, what's wrong?

813
00:54:12,270 --> 00:54:14,060
Are we there?

814
00:54:14,190 --> 00:54:16,470
No, it's a crossing.

815
00:54:19,470 --> 00:54:21,700
Will you tell me, where we're going now?

816
00:54:21,830 --> 00:54:24,140
What do you mean, where?

817
00:54:24,270 --> 00:54:27,070
You asked me a thousand times.
We're going...

818
00:54:27,190 --> 00:54:29,620
to the place... What's it called?

819
00:54:29,800 --> 00:54:31,380
We're going...

820
00:54:31,510 --> 00:54:33,630
Where are we going?

821
00:54:33,750 --> 00:54:37,460
What day is it today?
Today is your birthday!

822
00:54:37,590 --> 00:54:39,980
You've always said you
wanted, to go on a trip!

823
00:54:40,110 --> 00:54:43,070
It took me months to
plan this whole thing.

824
00:54:44,310 --> 00:54:46,460
You know where we're going?

825
00:54:46,590 --> 00:54:49,190
I can't tell you. I promised
Mom, I wouldn't tell.

826
00:54:49,310 --> 00:54:51,030
You know how she is. She'll get mad.

827
00:54:51,150 --> 00:54:53,150
It makes me laugh.

828
00:54:53,280 --> 00:54:56,500
My pop planned something like
this for me when I was little too.

829
00:54:59,200 --> 00:55:01,160
It was so... Boy, it was funny!

830
00:55:05,040 --> 00:55:08,350
I'm not going to tell you.
I want you to see for yourself.

831
00:55:08,480 --> 00:55:11,760
It's a surprise.
You know, it's really...

832
00:55:11,880 --> 00:55:13,310
It really makes me laugh.

833
00:55:14,640 --> 00:55:15,710
I'm tired.

834
00:55:15,840 --> 00:55:17,670
Go to sleep.

835
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:26,150
Where are we going?
Where are they taking us?

836
00:55:45,120 --> 00:55:48,750
What time is it?
We're leaving right on time.

837
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:50,520
What organization!

838
00:55:50,650 --> 00:55:53,160
- You've never taken a train, huh?
- No. Is it nice?

839
00:55:53,280 --> 00:55:54,680
It's really nice!

840
00:55:54,800 --> 00:55:57,880
It's all wooden inside. Everybody
stands up. There's not one seat.

841
00:55:58,000 --> 00:56:01,170
- There aren't any seats?
- What? Seats on a train?

842
00:56:01,300 --> 00:56:03,360
It's obvious, you've never been on one!

843
00:56:03,500 --> 00:56:06,570
No, everybody stands
real close together.

844
00:56:06,700 --> 00:56:08,130
Do you see this line?

845
00:56:08,170 --> 00:56:10,690
I got the last tickets just in time!

846
00:56:10,820 --> 00:56:14,010
Hurry up, Uncle Eliseo.
I don't want them to say, "Too late.

847
00:56:14,140 --> 00:56:15,650
It's full. Go back home."

848
00:56:15,780 --> 00:56:19,130
Wait up. We've got a reservation!
Leave some room for us!

849
00:56:19,250 --> 00:56:21,050
Look at this line!

850
00:56:22,780 --> 00:56:25,420
Here we are! We made a reservation!

851
00:56:27,900 --> 00:56:30,010
Thank you!

852
00:56:32,500 --> 00:56:37,050
- May I help you?
- There's been a mistake.

853
00:56:37,180 --> 00:56:39,570
What mistake?

854
00:56:39,700 --> 00:56:42,300
My husband and son are on that train.

855
00:56:43,420 --> 00:56:45,170
What's your husband's name?

856
00:56:45,300 --> 00:56:47,370
Guido Orefice.

857
00:56:53,260 --> 00:56:54,940
Joshua Orefice...

858
00:56:55,060 --> 00:56:58,900
and Eliseo Orefice
are on that train too.

859
00:56:59,020 --> 00:57:00,820
There's no mistake.

860
00:57:02,620 --> 00:57:04,500
I want to get on that train too.

861
00:57:06,420 --> 00:57:09,970
- We're all ready.
- Send them off then.

862
00:57:10,100 --> 00:57:11,380
Go, leave!

863
00:57:13,590 --> 00:57:16,710
Go back home, ma'am.

864
00:57:16,820 --> 00:57:18,340
I want to get on that train.

865
00:57:26,910 --> 00:57:29,500
Let me get on that train!

866
00:57:59,160 --> 00:58:00,120
Mom's here!

867
00:58:03,240 --> 00:58:06,520
They stopped the train,
to let Mom get on.

868
01:00:04,870 --> 01:00:06,350
Uncle Eliseo.

869
01:00:44,910 --> 01:00:48,150
Are you happy? Did you see
this place? Are you tired?

870
01:00:48,270 --> 01:00:51,510
- I didn't like the train.
- Me either.

871
01:00:51,630 --> 01:00:53,710
We'll take the bus back.

872
01:00:53,840 --> 01:00:57,910
We're taking the bus back!
The one with the seats in it!

873
01:00:58,030 --> 01:01:00,710
- I told them.
- It's better.

874
01:01:01,920 --> 01:01:04,910
You see? It's all organized!

875
01:01:05,040 --> 01:01:06,670
Did you see that line?

876
01:01:06,700 --> 01:01:09,270
People are lined up to get inside!

877
01:01:09,400 --> 01:01:12,760
- Everybody wants to get in!
- What game is this?

878
01:01:12,880 --> 01:01:14,520
That's it!

879
01:01:14,640 --> 01:01:16,990
It's that game where...

880
01:01:17,120 --> 01:01:19,350
It's the game...

881
01:01:19,480 --> 01:01:21,280
We're all players.

882
01:01:22,730 --> 01:01:25,170
It's all organized. The game is...

883
01:01:25,290 --> 01:01:28,280
the men are over here,
the women are over there.

884
01:01:28,410 --> 01:01:31,400
Then there's the soldiers.
They give us our schedule.

885
01:01:31,530 --> 01:01:33,880
It's hard, you know. It's not easy.

886
01:01:34,010 --> 01:01:37,560
If somebody makes a mistake,
they get sent right home.

887
01:01:37,690 --> 01:01:39,570
That means, you have to be very careful.

888
01:01:39,690 --> 01:01:43,000
But if you win, you get first prize!

889
01:01:43,130 --> 01:01:45,280
What's the prize?

890
01:01:45,410 --> 01:01:47,290
First prize!

891
01:01:48,740 --> 01:01:51,640
- It's a tank.
- I already have one.

892
01:01:51,770 --> 01:01:55,290
This one's a real tank! Brand new!

893
01:01:55,410 --> 01:01:57,450
Real?

894
01:01:57,580 --> 01:02:00,170
Yes! I didn't want to tell you.

895
01:02:07,410 --> 01:02:09,250
Where's Uncle Eliseo going?

896
01:02:09,370 --> 01:02:11,810
He's on another team.
It's all organized.

897
01:02:11,940 --> 01:02:13,930
Bye, Uncle!

898
01:02:16,650 --> 01:02:19,010
A real tank.

899
01:02:32,300 --> 01:02:34,010
What did I tell you?

900
01:02:34,980 --> 01:02:36,490
Fabulous!

901
01:02:36,620 --> 01:02:38,530
What a place!

902
01:02:38,660 --> 01:02:42,660
Hurry up or they'll steal our places.
We've got a reservation. Two singles!

903
01:02:43,700 --> 01:02:45,890
Coming through!

904
01:02:46,020 --> 01:02:48,210
There's our place!

905
01:02:53,220 --> 01:02:55,180
This is our bed. We'll sleep real close.

906
01:02:57,220 --> 01:03:00,660
It's ugly here. It smells.
I want to be with Mommy.

907
01:03:00,790 --> 01:03:02,700
We will be!

908
01:03:02,830 --> 01:03:05,420
- I'm hungry!
- We'll eat!

909
01:03:05,560 --> 01:03:08,670
Plus, they're really
mean here! They yell!

910
01:03:08,790 --> 01:03:11,440
They yell, because
everybody wants first prize.

911
01:03:11,470 --> 01:03:12,630
They have to be tough.

912
01:03:12,760 --> 01:03:17,390
- Can I see Mommy?
- When the game's over.

913
01:03:17,520 --> 01:03:18,750
When's it over?

914
01:03:20,750 --> 01:03:23,030
You have to get a thousand points.

915
01:03:24,430 --> 01:03:26,910
Whoever gets a thousand
points, wins a tank.

916
01:03:27,040 --> 01:03:29,710
I don't believe you.
Are we getting a snack?

917
01:03:29,830 --> 01:03:32,190
A snack?

918
01:03:32,310 --> 01:03:34,990
Just ask. We're all friends here.

919
01:03:35,120 --> 01:03:37,790
- Look who's here. What's his name?
- Bartolomeo.

920
01:03:37,920 --> 01:03:39,950
Let me ask you something.

921
01:03:40,080 --> 01:03:43,070
Did the guy who hands out the
bread and jam already come by?

922
01:03:44,440 --> 01:03:47,830
Darn it all! We missed him, by a second!

923
01:03:47,960 --> 01:03:51,270
He'll come back again though, won't he?

924
01:03:51,400 --> 01:03:53,960
He's coming back.

925
01:04:00,000 --> 01:04:02,880
- What did he say?
- He asked if anyone speaks German.

926
01:04:03,000 --> 01:04:05,070
He's going to explain the camp's rules.

927
01:04:08,400 --> 01:04:10,520
- Do you speak German?
- No.

928
01:04:19,650 --> 01:04:22,880
The game starts now. Whoever's
here is here, whoever's not is not.

929
01:04:26,370 --> 01:04:28,860
The first one to get,
a thousand points wins.

930
01:04:28,900 --> 01:04:29,920
The prize is a tank!

931
01:04:31,000 --> 01:04:31,990
Lucky him!

932
01:04:40,370 --> 01:04:44,160
Every day we'll announce, who's
in the lead from that loudspeaker.

933
01:04:44,290 --> 01:04:47,010
The one with the least points,
has to wear a sign saying "jackass"...

934
01:04:47,130 --> 01:04:48,360
right here on his back.

935
01:04:55,180 --> 01:04:57,900
We play the part, of the
real mean guys, who yell.

936
01:04:58,020 --> 01:04:59,370
Whoever's scared, loses points.

937
01:05:14,140 --> 01:05:17,450
You'll lose your points.
for three things.

938
01:05:17,580 --> 01:05:20,410
One: If you cry.

939
01:05:20,540 --> 01:05:23,300
Two: If you want to see your mommy.

940
01:05:23,420 --> 01:05:26,700
Three: If you're hungry
and you want a snack.

941
01:05:26,820 --> 01:05:28,260
Forget about it!

942
01:05:36,630 --> 01:05:39,060
It's easy to lose points,
for being hungry.

943
01:05:39,190 --> 01:05:41,260
Just yesterday, I lost 40 points...

944
01:05:41,390 --> 01:05:44,020
because I absolutely had
to have, a jam sandwich.

945
01:05:45,430 --> 01:05:48,820
Apricot jam! He wanted strawberry.

946
01:05:56,150 --> 01:05:58,740
Don't ask for any lollipops.
You won't get any.

947
01:05:58,870 --> 01:06:00,380
We eat them all!

948
01:06:02,470 --> 01:06:03,860
I ate 20 of them yesterday!

949
01:06:04,950 --> 01:06:08,470
What a stomachache.
But they sure were good.

950
01:06:09,550 --> 01:06:10,540
You bet.

951
01:06:18,910 --> 01:06:21,580
Sorry if I'm going so fast,
but I'm playing hide and seek.

952
01:06:21,710 --> 01:06:23,500
I have to go now or they'll find me.

953
01:06:33,190 --> 01:06:34,590
Don't ask me anything.

954
01:06:34,620 --> 01:06:36,980
Ask Bartolomeo. He knows everything.

955
01:06:37,110 --> 01:06:39,350
Don't forget to tell me,
what he said too.

956
01:06:39,470 --> 01:06:41,300
A thousand points?

957
01:06:41,430 --> 01:06:43,670
I told you, we're going to have fun!

958
01:06:43,800 --> 01:06:45,950
These guys are crazy!

959
01:06:46,080 --> 01:06:49,790
This has to weigh a hundred kilos!
It's got to be 3,000 degrees in here!

960
01:06:49,920 --> 01:06:52,280
Vittorino, I can't cope anymore!

961
01:06:52,400 --> 01:06:55,120
- After only the first one?
- Why, are there more to move?

962
01:06:55,250 --> 01:06:57,400
We're here until tonight!

963
01:06:57,530 --> 01:07:00,720
Bartolomeo, what happened?
Where are they taking you?

964
01:07:00,840 --> 01:07:03,410
To the hospital. I hurt my arm.

965
01:07:04,850 --> 01:07:06,880
We're going to die here!

966
01:07:08,010 --> 01:07:10,840
I can't take it anymore!
I'm putting this down.

967
01:07:10,970 --> 01:07:13,320
I'll tell them I can't do it.
What can they do to me?

968
01:07:13,450 --> 01:07:15,880
They'll kill you!

969
01:07:18,250 --> 01:07:20,200
- Where does this thing go?
- Down there.

970
01:07:20,330 --> 01:07:22,890
Good Lord! I'll never make it!

971
01:07:30,770 --> 01:07:32,880
It's got to be 10,000 degrees in here!

972
01:08:02,140 --> 01:08:03,360
Pop!

973
01:08:18,340 --> 01:08:21,140
Look here! See? It's nice, huh?

974
01:08:23,540 --> 01:08:25,580
We're signed up.

975
01:08:25,700 --> 01:08:28,860
When I got there to sign up...

976
01:08:28,990 --> 01:08:31,630
the referee was there and he said...

977
01:08:31,750 --> 01:08:34,340
"No, you and your son
aren't on the list.

978
01:08:34,470 --> 01:08:36,700
You didn't pay your dues."

979
01:08:36,830 --> 01:08:38,740
I almost fell over.

980
01:08:38,870 --> 01:08:41,860
He said, "You can go home."
I said, "No, you go home!

981
01:08:41,990 --> 01:08:44,590
Joshua and I signed up.

982
01:08:44,710 --> 01:08:49,420
Give me my number!"
In fact, they gave me one. Look.

983
01:08:49,550 --> 01:08:53,060
I had them put it here,
too, just in case.

984
01:08:53,190 --> 01:08:55,150
See what a nice place...

985
01:08:56,230 --> 01:08:58,190
your pop takes you to?

986
01:09:00,270 --> 01:09:02,870
Did you play with the other kids?

987
01:09:02,990 --> 01:09:05,510
Yes, but they don't know the rules.

988
01:09:06,390 --> 01:09:09,110
They said it isn't true,
that first prize is a tank.

989
01:09:09,240 --> 01:09:11,300
They don't know anything,
about the points.

990
01:09:11,430 --> 01:09:14,790
Did you fall for that?
They're as sly as foxes.

991
01:09:14,920 --> 01:09:16,830
They want to beat you! Are you joking?

992
01:09:16,960 --> 01:09:20,390
There's no tank? Don't you believe them!

993
01:09:20,520 --> 01:09:23,270
How many points, did we get today?

994
01:09:23,400 --> 01:09:25,150
Fifty.

995
01:09:25,280 --> 01:09:28,030
Forty-eight. They took two
points away from me, because...

996
01:09:28,160 --> 01:09:30,220
I tripped, while I was...

997
01:09:30,350 --> 01:09:32,470
playing hopscotch.

998
01:09:33,640 --> 01:09:35,230
We...

999
01:09:35,360 --> 01:09:38,950
laughed like crazy today!
I died laughing!

1000
01:09:39,080 --> 01:09:40,880
Boy, did I have fun!

1001
01:09:41,000 --> 01:09:43,280
I can't wait to start
all over again, tomorrow!

1002
01:09:43,400 --> 01:09:46,950
Hopscotch, tug of war and
ring around the rosy.

1003
01:09:47,080 --> 01:09:49,230
Every game. I don't even
remember all of them.

1004
01:09:49,360 --> 01:09:52,870
"You guys are obsessed!
Stop! I'm tired!", I said.

1005
01:09:53,000 --> 01:09:54,800
Listen.

1006
01:09:54,920 --> 01:09:58,310
- Did you eat something?
- Yes, but I didn't ask for a snack.

1007
01:09:58,440 --> 01:10:02,280
Good boy! That means
you got 12 points too!

1008
01:10:02,400 --> 01:10:04,600
Forty-eight for me, 12 for you.

1009
01:10:04,720 --> 01:10:05,920
Sixty points.

1010
01:10:06,040 --> 01:10:09,080
This is what you get,
when you get up to 60.

1011
01:10:09,200 --> 01:10:12,410
A plain piece of bread, no jam.

1012
01:10:12,530 --> 01:10:14,520
Here, eat this.

1013
01:10:17,050 --> 01:10:20,490
- Is 60 points a lot?
- Are you kidding?

1014
01:10:20,620 --> 01:10:22,050
It sure is!

1015
01:10:25,690 --> 01:10:28,080
Look who's here! Bartolomeo!

1016
01:10:28,210 --> 01:10:29,200
How'd it go?

1017
01:10:30,540 --> 01:10:33,330
Any worse than this... I got 20 of them.

1018
01:10:37,010 --> 01:10:39,530
We got more than him.

1019
01:10:39,660 --> 01:10:41,880
Don't tell him that. We're in the lead!

1020
01:10:51,340 --> 01:10:53,770
I already told you:
No children or old ladies!

1021
01:10:53,900 --> 01:10:56,730
Back inside! You don't work!

1022
01:10:56,860 --> 01:10:59,290
The rest, downstairs!

1023
01:10:59,420 --> 01:11:02,220
Let's go, girls, quickly.
Come on. This way!

1024
01:11:03,540 --> 01:11:06,140
That one's new. She learned right away.

1025
01:11:06,260 --> 01:11:07,520
The lady at the door...

1026
01:11:07,530 --> 01:11:09,570
she seemed nice, when she first came.

1027
01:11:09,700 --> 01:11:11,420
She's the worst of all!

1028
01:11:11,540 --> 01:11:14,180
At least she didn't send the
old ladies and children to work.

1029
01:11:14,300 --> 01:11:17,690
They don't send old people and
kids to work, because they kill them!

1030
01:11:17,820 --> 01:11:20,420
One of these days, they'll
call them to take a shower.

1031
01:11:20,540 --> 01:11:22,260
"Children, shower time!"

1032
01:11:22,380 --> 01:11:25,740
The truth is, they make them
shower, there in the gas chamber.

1033
01:11:32,870 --> 01:11:34,460
Downstairs!

1034
01:11:38,140 --> 01:11:40,820
How can I do this?

1035
01:11:40,940 --> 01:11:42,420
Vittorino!

1036
01:11:43,860 --> 01:11:46,170
Where'd they find all these anvils?

1037
01:11:46,300 --> 01:11:48,060
Pop!

1038
01:11:49,740 --> 01:11:52,100
Why are you here?
You're not supposed to be here!

1039
01:11:52,220 --> 01:11:53,870
Go away!

1040
01:11:53,990 --> 01:11:56,220
Why aren't you, with the other kids?

1041
01:11:56,350 --> 01:11:58,020
They said...

1042
01:11:58,150 --> 01:12:01,110
all us kids have to take a
shower today, and I don't want to.

1043
01:12:02,710 --> 01:12:04,590
- Go take a shower!
- No!

1044
01:12:05,640 --> 01:12:07,510
I'm not going to.

1045
01:12:07,640 --> 01:12:09,070
Go take a shower!

1046
01:12:10,160 --> 01:12:11,640
What are you doing here?

1047
01:12:13,840 --> 01:12:18,350
We're making... a tank.

1048
01:12:18,480 --> 01:12:21,550
We're building the tank.
We're still working on the tracks.

1049
01:12:21,680 --> 01:12:23,430
We're running slow.

1050
01:12:25,120 --> 01:12:28,000
You can't stay here.
Go take your shower!

1051
01:12:28,120 --> 01:12:31,000
I don't want to!

1052
01:12:31,120 --> 01:12:33,230
You stubborn thing! I'll tell Mom!

1053
01:12:33,260 --> 01:12:34,670
Ten points off for you!

1054
01:12:34,800 --> 01:12:35,760
Hide behind there.

1055
01:12:35,800 --> 01:12:37,880
We'll go back together, when I'm done.

1056
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:39,800
Don't let anyone see you!

1057
01:12:39,920 --> 01:12:41,720
This sure is fun.

1058
01:12:55,280 --> 01:12:56,640
Everything!

1059
01:12:56,770 --> 01:12:59,200
Take everything off! Hang it up there!

1060
01:12:59,320 --> 01:13:02,360
You'll get it back, after the shower.

1061
01:13:02,480 --> 01:13:03,680
Forward!

1062
01:13:05,610 --> 01:13:07,960
Remember your number,
to get your clothes back!

1063
01:13:11,410 --> 01:13:14,400
Women and children, will shower together.

1064
01:13:14,530 --> 01:13:16,440
Are you hurt?

1065
01:13:26,930 --> 01:13:28,760
Thanks, Bartolomeo.

1066
01:13:28,890 --> 01:13:31,650
From now on, you have to
hide here, the whole day.

1067
01:13:31,770 --> 01:13:34,200
If they see us now it's over.
We're disqualified.

1068
01:13:34,330 --> 01:13:36,000
What do I have to do?

1069
01:13:36,130 --> 01:13:38,360
You have to stay.
Vittorino, help me out.

1070
01:13:38,490 --> 01:13:40,410
You have to hide here, all day.

1071
01:13:40,530 --> 01:13:44,690
Don't let anyone see you,
especially those mean guys who yell.

1072
01:13:44,810 --> 01:13:46,040
Remember.

1073
01:13:46,170 --> 01:13:47,930
Stay hidden!

1074
01:13:48,050 --> 01:13:50,580
This is the hardest part.

1075
01:13:50,710 --> 01:13:55,060
If we get this right, the tank is ours.
It's worth 120 points a day.

1076
01:13:55,190 --> 01:13:57,910
I'll take you with me.
I'll hide you. You're gone.

1077
01:13:58,020 --> 01:14:00,780
Who's ever seen you before?
Who are you? Where is he?

1078
01:14:00,910 --> 01:14:02,180
Got it?

1079
01:14:07,260 --> 01:14:08,420
Got ya!

1080
01:14:10,190 --> 01:14:11,510
Good boy!

1081
01:15:25,360 --> 01:15:27,790
Anybody here? Am I disturbing?

1082
01:15:35,640 --> 01:15:37,640
Come here!

1083
01:15:37,770 --> 01:15:39,640
Quick as lightning!

1084
01:15:45,410 --> 01:15:47,050
Good morning, Princess!

1085
01:15:47,170 --> 01:15:51,050
Last night, I dreamt
about you all night!

1086
01:15:51,170 --> 01:15:55,320
We were going to the movies.
You were wearing that pink suit...

1087
01:15:55,450 --> 01:15:57,010
that I really like.

1088
01:15:57,130 --> 01:15:59,360
You're all I think about, Princess.

1089
01:15:59,490 --> 01:16:01,960
I always think about you. And now...

1090
01:16:02,090 --> 01:16:03,520
Mommy!

1091
01:16:03,650 --> 01:16:07,490
Pop wheels me in the wheelbarrow,
but he doesn't know, how to drive!

1092
01:16:07,610 --> 01:16:08,960
We laugh like crazy!

1093
01:16:09,090 --> 01:16:12,720
We're in the lead! How many
points do we have today?

1094
01:16:12,850 --> 01:16:16,080
Run! The mean guys,
who yell, are behind us!

1095
01:16:16,090 --> 01:16:18,450
- Where?
- Over here! Come on!

1096
01:16:31,580 --> 01:16:33,450
Are they dry?

1097
01:16:35,180 --> 01:16:36,650
They're dry.

1098
01:16:36,780 --> 01:16:38,410
Catch.

1099
01:16:38,540 --> 01:16:40,050
Get dressed.

1100
01:16:53,740 --> 01:16:57,130
What happened to Vittorino,
Alfonso and the others?

1101
01:16:57,260 --> 01:16:59,460
They didn't make it.

1102
01:17:49,680 --> 01:17:53,060
"If you say my name,
I'm not there anymore."

1103
01:17:53,190 --> 01:17:54,420
Silence.

1104
01:18:26,240 --> 01:18:28,830
Thank goodness. I was getting scared.
What happened to you?

1105
01:18:28,960 --> 01:18:31,080
They're half crazy!

1106
01:18:33,480 --> 01:18:35,550
The man who does the
check-ups, the Captain...

1107
01:18:35,680 --> 01:18:38,350
He's a friend of mine.
I met him when I was a waiter.

1108
01:18:38,490 --> 01:18:42,440
He said they're having a dinner with
all the officials and their wives.

1109
01:18:42,570 --> 01:18:45,840
He asked me if I wanted to
wait tables, at the dinner.

1110
01:18:45,970 --> 01:18:49,680
Maybe he wants to help me.
He might get us out of here.

1111
01:18:55,850 --> 01:18:57,880
Have you seen Joshua?

1112
01:18:58,000 --> 01:18:59,800
What do you mean, no?

1113
01:19:06,890 --> 01:19:08,840
What are you doing? Come here!

1114
01:19:08,970 --> 01:19:13,020
- No.
- I told you to come.

1115
01:19:13,140 --> 01:19:14,620
No? Come on out!

1116
01:19:15,690 --> 01:19:18,010
Come out! Look here. You're all dirty.

1117
01:19:19,100 --> 01:19:20,330
Where have you been?

1118
01:19:21,580 --> 01:19:23,930
I had to finish playing rummy.

1119
01:19:24,900 --> 01:19:27,890
They make buttons and soap out of us.

1120
01:19:30,100 --> 01:19:33,540
- What are you saying?
- They burn us all in the oven.

1121
01:19:34,540 --> 01:19:36,770
Who told you that?

1122
01:19:36,900 --> 01:19:41,500
A man was crying. He said they
make buttons and soap out of us.

1123
01:19:44,020 --> 01:19:46,090
You fell for that?

1124
01:19:46,220 --> 01:19:48,290
Again?

1125
01:19:48,420 --> 01:19:51,580
I thought you were a sharp boy...
cunning, intelligent.

1126
01:19:51,700 --> 01:19:55,460
Buttons and soap out of people?
That'll be the day!

1127
01:19:55,580 --> 01:19:57,940
You believed that?

1128
01:19:58,780 --> 01:20:02,660
Just imagine. Tomorrow morning,
I wash my hands with Bartolomeo...

1129
01:20:02,790 --> 01:20:04,340
a good scrub.

1130
01:20:04,460 --> 01:20:07,100
Then I'll button up with Francesco.

1131
01:20:07,230 --> 01:20:08,370
Darn it all!

1132
01:20:08,500 --> 01:20:10,940
Look! I just lost Giorgio!

1133
01:20:11,060 --> 01:20:13,220
Does this look like a person?

1134
01:20:13,350 --> 01:20:16,220
Come on! They were teasing you!
And you fell for it!

1135
01:20:16,350 --> 01:20:18,460
What else did they tell you?

1136
01:20:18,590 --> 01:20:20,380
That we get cooked in the oven.

1137
01:20:24,270 --> 01:20:26,140
They burn us up in the oven.

1138
01:20:29,710 --> 01:20:32,660
You fell for that too!
You just eat everything up!

1139
01:20:32,790 --> 01:20:34,940
I've heard of a wood oven...

1140
01:20:35,070 --> 01:20:36,980
but I've never seen a man oven before.

1141
01:20:37,910 --> 01:20:41,510
"I'm made of wood!" - "Take this lawyer!"

1142
01:20:41,630 --> 01:20:43,980
"This lawyer doesn't burn.
He's not dry enough.

1143
01:20:44,110 --> 01:20:45,670
Look at that smoke!"

1144
01:20:47,190 --> 01:20:49,830
Buttons, soap, we get
burned in the oven.

1145
01:20:49,950 --> 01:20:51,910
Let's be serious now.

1146
01:20:52,030 --> 01:20:54,670
I have a bag race,
with the bad guys tomorrow.

1147
01:20:54,790 --> 01:20:58,160
That's enough. I want to go home.

1148
01:20:59,960 --> 01:21:02,470
- Now?
- Right now.

1149
01:21:02,600 --> 01:21:05,680
It's raining now. You'll come
down with a terrible fever!

1150
01:21:05,800 --> 01:21:07,560
I don't care. Let's go.

1151
01:21:08,840 --> 01:21:11,230
All right. If you want to go...

1152
01:21:12,480 --> 01:21:14,280
I'll get our stuff and we'll leave.

1153
01:21:15,530 --> 01:21:17,680
- We can leave?
- Naturally.

1154
01:21:17,800 --> 01:21:20,160
What do you think they do,
force people to stay here?

1155
01:21:20,290 --> 01:21:22,200
That'll be the day.

1156
01:21:22,330 --> 01:21:24,050
Wouldn't that be great? Let's go.

1157
01:21:24,080 --> 01:21:25,210
We'll pack our bags...

1158
01:21:25,320 --> 01:21:27,840
and get out of here.

1159
01:21:27,970 --> 01:21:31,560
What a shame. We were in the lead.
We're quitting. Off the list we go.

1160
01:21:31,690 --> 01:21:34,560
Some other kid, will win the real tank.

1161
01:21:34,690 --> 01:21:37,520
There aren't any other kids.
I'm the only one left.

1162
01:21:37,650 --> 01:21:40,720
There aren't any more kids?
It's chock-full of them here!

1163
01:21:40,850 --> 01:21:42,280
Where are they then?

1164
01:21:42,410 --> 01:21:45,050
They're all hiding.
Nobody's supposed to see them.

1165
01:21:45,170 --> 01:21:48,950
- This is a serious game!
- I just don't get it.

1166
01:21:49,090 --> 01:21:50,970
How many points do we have?

1167
01:21:51,090 --> 01:21:53,080
Almost 687.

1168
01:21:53,210 --> 01:21:55,090
I told you a thousand times.

1169
01:21:55,890 --> 01:21:57,240
Let's go, though.

1170
01:21:57,370 --> 01:22:00,200
- We're winning, but if you want...
- We're winning?

1171
01:22:00,330 --> 01:22:04,560
We're first, I told you.
But we'll quit if you want.

1172
01:22:05,410 --> 01:22:08,250
I saw the chart yesterday.
We'll go anyway, though.

1173
01:22:08,370 --> 01:22:10,170
Bye, Bartolomeo.
Joshua and I are leaving.

1174
01:22:10,290 --> 01:22:12,010
We're fed up here.

1175
01:22:13,650 --> 01:22:16,080
The tank is done. It's ready.

1176
01:22:16,210 --> 01:22:18,970
Clean the spark plugs off,
before you start it.

1177
01:22:19,090 --> 01:22:21,660
Open the throttle...

1178
01:22:21,770 --> 01:22:24,730
otherwise the cannon will
get stuck, with the tracks.

1179
01:22:24,860 --> 01:22:27,430
And the gun. Did you see how nice it is?

1180
01:22:27,470 --> 01:22:28,850
It came out beautiful!

1181
01:22:28,970 --> 01:22:32,570
Lift the emergency brake off,
before you move! We're going.

1182
01:22:32,700 --> 01:22:34,650
Joshua wants to quit.

1183
01:22:34,780 --> 01:22:38,090
We could have gone back with a tank
soon, but we'll take the bus today.

1184
01:22:38,220 --> 01:22:40,410
Joshua and I are leaving.
So long, everybody!

1185
01:22:40,530 --> 01:22:42,330
We're tired of this place.

1186
01:22:42,460 --> 01:22:45,050
Let's go or we'll miss the bus.

1187
01:22:50,710 --> 01:22:52,060
Let's go, Joshua.

1188
01:22:55,390 --> 01:22:58,980
It's raining. I'll come
down with a terrible fever!

1189
01:24:06,560 --> 01:24:08,710
It's me, Pop!

1190
01:24:08,840 --> 01:24:11,830
I have to tell you something
important! Come here!

1191
01:24:11,960 --> 01:24:14,520
That little rascal's, been
running away all morning.

1192
01:24:14,640 --> 01:24:17,200
- Is there really a kid?
- There must be two thousand!

1193
01:24:17,320 --> 01:24:19,310
They're like mice.
They hide all over the place!

1194
01:24:19,440 --> 01:24:22,080
Those creeps want our tank! Stop!

1195
01:24:22,200 --> 01:24:23,520
Wait.

1196
01:24:25,320 --> 01:24:27,150
I might have spotted him.

1197
01:24:27,280 --> 01:24:29,590
I think he's nearby.

1198
01:24:29,720 --> 01:24:33,570
Look. Go see if he's hiding
in there. I'll wait here.

1199
01:24:33,690 --> 01:24:35,600
I'll keep a watch out.

1200
01:24:41,890 --> 01:24:43,450
He's there, Pop!

1201
01:24:43,570 --> 01:24:45,560
- What'd he look like? Blond?
- Yes.

1202
01:24:45,690 --> 01:24:48,210
That's him then. His name is... Schwanz.

1203
01:24:48,330 --> 01:24:50,410
He's been in there for three weeks.

1204
01:24:50,540 --> 01:24:52,970
He was the runner up.
We beat him, though!

1205
01:24:53,090 --> 01:24:55,810
Sooner or later,
I'll find the others too.

1206
01:24:55,940 --> 01:24:58,400
- How many are there?
- It's swarming, I told you.

1207
01:24:58,530 --> 01:25:00,130
They're all hidden.

1208
01:25:09,210 --> 01:25:12,020
- Look, Pop!
- There's a hideout!

1209
01:25:13,980 --> 01:25:15,810
Got ya, got ya, got ya!
You're out! Let's go.

1210
01:25:22,980 --> 01:25:26,180
- Holy smokes! She saw us!
- Are we out?

1211
01:25:26,300 --> 01:25:28,610
She's coming over for you.

1212
01:25:28,740 --> 01:25:30,540
Now it's time for the "be quiet" game.

1213
01:25:30,660 --> 01:25:33,410
You're never to speak.

1214
01:25:33,540 --> 01:25:35,170
Swear it!

1215
01:25:36,260 --> 01:25:38,250
- Swear it!
- I swear.

1216
01:25:41,180 --> 01:25:43,490
They all talk strange.
You can't understand a word.

1217
01:25:43,620 --> 01:25:46,060
If we get through this,
the first prize is ours.

1218
01:25:46,180 --> 01:25:49,060
They're rounding up everyone in
first place. It's the silence game.

1219
01:25:49,180 --> 01:25:50,380
Not a word, got it?

1220
01:25:58,020 --> 01:25:59,820
Why are you here, with the children?

1221
01:25:59,940 --> 01:26:01,740
Quiet! You're never to speak.

1222
01:26:03,140 --> 01:26:04,340
I swear.

1223
01:26:58,200 --> 01:27:01,000
I have to talk to you. Very important.

1224
01:27:01,120 --> 01:27:04,000
- Where? When?
- I'll signal you. Later.

1225
01:27:16,690 --> 01:27:17,920
Thank you.

1226
01:28:02,490 --> 01:28:04,840
I told you not to talk to the children.

1227
01:28:31,620 --> 01:28:34,220
Doctor, my wife is here too.

1228
01:28:55,910 --> 01:28:57,310
Slowly.

1229
01:28:57,430 --> 01:28:59,870
Eat slowly. It's bad for you.

1230
01:28:59,990 --> 01:29:03,870
We're in the lead.
We just might leave early.

1231
01:29:03,990 --> 01:29:06,100
The game finishes early.

1232
01:29:06,230 --> 01:29:09,060
Don't make a mistake now
that we're in the lead.

1233
01:29:09,190 --> 01:29:10,510
Slowly.

1234
01:29:31,870 --> 01:29:33,670
So. Pay attention.

1235
01:29:39,190 --> 01:29:42,950
"Fat, fat, ugly, ugly,
all yellow in reality.

1236
01:29:44,640 --> 01:29:46,590
If you ask me what I am...

1237
01:29:46,720 --> 01:29:49,310
I answer, 'Cheep, cheep, cheep'.

1238
01:29:54,850 --> 01:29:58,200
Walking along I go, 'Poopoo'.

1239
01:29:58,320 --> 01:30:00,710
Who am I? Tell me true."

1240
01:30:05,050 --> 01:30:06,770
A duckling, right?

1241
01:30:09,770 --> 01:30:11,570
Is it a duckling?

1242
01:30:13,130 --> 01:30:15,570
It's not!

1243
01:30:16,570 --> 01:30:19,720
A veterinarian friend of mine
sent it to me from Vienna.

1244
01:30:19,850 --> 01:30:22,200
I can't send him mine...

1245
01:30:22,330 --> 01:30:24,680
until I solve this one.

1246
01:30:25,770 --> 01:30:27,720
I thought...

1247
01:30:27,850 --> 01:30:29,970
duck-billed platypus...

1248
01:30:30,090 --> 01:30:32,000
but it doesn't go,
"Cheep, cheep, cheep".

1249
01:30:32,130 --> 01:30:34,330
A duck-billed platypus goes...

1250
01:30:39,850 --> 01:30:43,400
I translated it into
Italian, for you last night.

1251
01:30:45,330 --> 01:30:47,130
Well, what do you say?

1252
01:30:49,300 --> 01:30:51,570
Everything points, to a duckling.

1253
01:30:53,780 --> 01:30:55,410
Help me.

1254
01:30:58,930 --> 01:31:00,930
For heaven's sake...

1255
01:31:01,060 --> 01:31:03,090
help me.

1256
01:31:03,210 --> 01:31:05,330
I can't even sleep.

1257
01:31:21,460 --> 01:31:23,770
It's the duckling!

1258
01:33:43,570 --> 01:33:45,220
Come here!

1259
01:33:47,410 --> 01:33:49,940
- I'm tired.
- Come here.

1260
01:33:55,740 --> 01:33:57,530
Where are we here?

1261
01:33:57,660 --> 01:34:00,380
I might have taken the wrong way.

1262
01:34:00,500 --> 01:34:03,460
Good boy, sleep. Dream sweet dreams.

1263
01:34:03,580 --> 01:34:05,810
Maybe it's only a dream!

1264
01:34:05,940 --> 01:34:07,930
We're dreaming, Joshua.

1265
01:34:08,060 --> 01:34:10,450
Tomorrow morning Mommy
will come wake us up...

1266
01:34:10,580 --> 01:34:14,650
and bring us two nice
cups of milk and cookies.

1267
01:34:14,780 --> 01:34:16,780
First, we'll eat.

1268
01:34:16,900 --> 01:34:19,700
Then I'll make love to her,
two or three times...

1269
01:34:20,540 --> 01:34:22,020
if I can.

1270
01:35:09,190 --> 01:35:11,230
Excuse me, Bartolomeo.

1271
01:35:11,350 --> 01:35:13,780
They've called those
two officers, 20 times.

1272
01:35:13,820 --> 01:35:14,780
I bet they escaped.

1273
01:35:14,910 --> 01:35:18,990
- Did you understand anything else?
- It's clear enough.

1274
01:35:19,120 --> 01:35:19,870
The war is over.

1275
01:35:19,910 --> 01:35:21,640
They're running all over the place.

1276
01:35:21,760 --> 01:35:24,120
Where are those trucks going?

1277
01:35:24,240 --> 01:35:26,880
The important thing is not,
to get on those trucks.

1278
01:35:27,000 --> 01:35:29,070
They leave full and come back empty.

1279
01:35:29,200 --> 01:35:31,000
You know where they're going?

1280
01:35:32,520 --> 01:35:34,640
What about the women? What's going on?

1281
01:35:34,760 --> 01:35:37,520
Let's get out of this dump and split up.

1282
01:35:37,640 --> 01:35:39,680
We don't even have to pack our bags!

1283
01:35:39,810 --> 01:35:42,270
I've been hearing only
dogs and machine guns.

1284
01:35:42,400 --> 01:35:45,470
- They want to get rid of everything.
- I'm leaving.

1285
01:35:45,600 --> 01:35:48,960
See you in Viareggio.
We'll start an anvil factory!

1286
01:35:49,090 --> 01:35:50,410
So long, guys. I'm leaving.

1287
01:36:07,210 --> 01:36:08,800
Come see.

1288
01:36:08,930 --> 01:36:11,520
Look how mad they are! Furious!

1289
01:36:12,810 --> 01:36:15,000
You see? They're looking for you.

1290
01:36:15,130 --> 01:36:17,120
Just for you. All this is over you!

1291
01:36:17,250 --> 01:36:19,160
You're the last one!
The last one to find!

1292
01:36:19,290 --> 01:36:22,360
They're even looking under the rocks!

1293
01:36:22,490 --> 01:36:25,130
The game is over tomorrow.
They'll give the award.

1294
01:36:25,250 --> 01:36:28,370
If they don't find you tonight,
it's worth 60 points!

1295
01:36:28,490 --> 01:36:30,160
How many points do we have?

1296
01:36:30,290 --> 01:36:33,210
We've got 940 points. Plus 60?

1297
01:36:33,330 --> 01:36:35,480
- A thousand!
- First place! We win!

1298
01:36:35,610 --> 01:36:37,920
They're looking all over for you.

1299
01:36:38,050 --> 01:36:40,280
No mistakes tonight. This is it!

1300
01:36:40,410 --> 01:36:43,690
- Go hide in that box, quick!
- Schwanz is in there.

1301
01:36:43,810 --> 01:36:45,530
Who?

1302
01:36:45,650 --> 01:36:47,840
The blond boy.

1303
01:36:50,060 --> 01:36:52,440
They got him yesterday.
He was eliminated.

1304
01:36:52,570 --> 01:36:55,220
It's the safest place to hide.
Nobody will look.

1305
01:36:55,330 --> 01:36:58,050
Let's go, quick as lightning. Come on!

1306
01:37:01,500 --> 01:37:03,260
Inside!

1307
01:37:03,390 --> 01:37:06,180
Take this blanket, in case you get cold.

1308
01:37:06,310 --> 01:37:08,420
I'll be back soon.

1309
01:37:08,550 --> 01:37:11,770
I'll put them on the wrong track.
I think I saw him over there!

1310
01:37:40,150 --> 01:37:43,380
Pop, you scared me to death!

1311
01:37:43,510 --> 01:37:45,460
Give me the blanket. Are you cold?

1312
01:37:45,590 --> 01:37:47,390
Give me your sweater then.

1313
01:37:47,510 --> 01:37:50,420
I'll throw it on a tree
and put them off track.

1314
01:37:50,550 --> 01:37:53,390
They're looking all over for you!

1315
01:37:53,510 --> 01:37:55,980
Everybody's yelling, "Where's Joshua?".

1316
01:37:56,110 --> 01:37:59,580
They're even cursing.
They're really, really mad!

1317
01:37:59,710 --> 01:38:02,870
No one will find you.
Bye, now. I'll be back later.

1318
01:38:03,830 --> 01:38:05,500
Listen...

1319
01:38:05,630 --> 01:38:08,630
if I'm really late coming back...

1320
01:38:08,750 --> 01:38:10,500
don't you move.

1321
01:38:10,630 --> 01:38:13,710
Don't come out.
You're not to come out...

1322
01:38:13,840 --> 01:38:17,150
until it's completely quiet...

1323
01:38:17,280 --> 01:38:19,350
and nobody is in sight, just to be safe.

1324
01:38:19,480 --> 01:38:20,750
Say it!

1325
01:38:20,880 --> 01:38:24,020
I won't come out until nobody is around.

1326
01:38:24,150 --> 01:38:26,060
Good boy, stubborn.

1327
01:38:53,890 --> 01:38:55,240
Leave!

1328
01:38:55,370 --> 01:38:57,360
Go away, dog!

1329
01:38:57,490 --> 01:38:59,400
Go, dog!

1330
01:38:59,530 --> 01:39:00,850
Leave.

1331
01:39:13,290 --> 01:39:14,810
Good job, Ferruccio.

1332
01:39:14,930 --> 01:39:16,810
It works.

1333
01:39:40,490 --> 01:39:42,490
Is there anyone called Dora here?

1334
01:40:20,940 --> 01:40:22,900
Dora, are you here? It's Guido.

1335
01:40:23,980 --> 01:40:27,260
I know someone is hiding here.
Is there a Dora here?

1336
01:40:36,350 --> 01:40:39,150
Is there a Dora here?
She's Italian. She's my wife.

1337
01:40:39,270 --> 01:40:42,100
Yes, there's a Dora here.

1338
01:40:43,070 --> 01:40:44,870
It's me, Dora!

1339
01:40:46,280 --> 01:40:48,390
It's not her! Is there another Dora?

1340
01:40:48,510 --> 01:40:50,660
Jump out of the truck,
as soon as you can!

1341
01:40:50,800 --> 01:40:53,030
Get off! Jump out!

1342
01:45:58,340 --> 01:46:00,220
It's true!

1343
01:47:16,960 --> 01:47:18,360
Mommy!

1344
01:47:29,480 --> 01:47:32,160
This is my story.

1345
01:47:33,640 --> 01:47:36,200
This is the sacrifice my father made.

1346
01:47:38,440 --> 01:47:40,640
This was his gift to me.

1347
01:47:40,760 --> 01:47:43,040
- We won!
- Yes, we won!

1348
01:47:45,140 --> 01:47:48,010
A thousand points to
laugh like crazy about!

1349
01:47:49,090 --> 01:47:52,640
We came in first!
We're taking the tank home!

1350
01:47:52,770 --> 01:47:55,050
We won!

